    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "As Stephen stood face to face with his judges to answer to the charge of blasphemy, a holy radiance shone upon his countenance, and &ldquo;all that sat in the council, looking steadfastly on him, saw his face as it had been the face of an angel.&rdquo; Many who beheld this light trembled and veiled their faces, but the stubborn unbelief and prejudice of the rulers did not waver.",
